## 3. Technical Decisions

### 3.1 Path Alias Configuration

**Decision:** Use `@/` prefix for all `src/` imports.

**Configuration:**

```json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "baseUrl": ".",
    "paths": {
      "@/*": ["./src/*"]
    }
  }
}
```

**Rationale:**

| Factor | Decision |
|--------|----------|
| Convention | `@/` is the Next.js standard (used in official examples) |
| Simplicity | Single prefix reduces cognitive load |
| Tool Support | Native support in Next.js, VS Code, ESLint |
| Refactoring | Easier file moves without breaking imports |

**Usage Examples:**

```typescript
// ✅ ALLOWED
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { apiClient } from '@/services/apiClient';
import { useAuth } from '@/hooks/useAuth';

// ❌ FORBIDDEN
import { Button } from '../../../components/ui/button';
import { Button } from 'src/components/ui/button';
```

