### 3.2 TypeScript Compiler Configuration

**Decision:** Strict TypeScript with Next.js optimizations.

**Full `tsconfig.json` Specification:**

```json
{
  "$schema": "https://json.schemastore.org/tsconfig",
  "compilerOptions": {
    // Strict Type Checking
    "strict": true,
    "noUncheckedIndexedAccess": true,
    "noImplicitOverride": true,
    "noPropertyAccessFromIndexSignature": true,
    
    // Module Resolution
    "target": "ES2022",
    "lib": ["dom", "dom.iterable", "ES2022"],
    "module": "esnext",
    "moduleResolution": "bundler",
    "resolveJsonModule": true,
    "isolatedModules": true,
    
    // Path Aliases
    "baseUrl": ".",
    "paths": {
      "@/*": ["./src/*"]
    },
    
    // Next.js Requirements
    "jsx": "preserve",
    "incremental": true,
    "esModuleInterop": true,
    "allowSyntheticDefaultImports": true,
    "skipLibCheck": true,
    "forceConsistentCasingInFileNames": true,
    "noEmit": true,
    
    // Plugin
    "plugins": [
      {
        "name": "next"
      }
    ]
  },
  "include": [
    "next-env.d.ts",
    "**/*.ts",
    "**/*.tsx",
    ".next/types/**/*.ts"
  ],
  "exclude": [
    "node_modules"
  ]
}
```

**Rationale for Key Options:**

| Option | Value | Rationale |
|--------|-------|-----------|
| `strict` | `true` | CODEBASE_GOVERNANCE_RULES §3.1 mandate |
| `noUncheckedIndexedAccess` | `true` | Prevents runtime undefined errors on arrays/objects |
| `noImplicitOverride` | `true` | Explicit override keyword prevents accidental overrides |
| `noPropertyAccessFromIndexSignature` | `true` | Forces bracket notation for dynamic keys |
| `target` | `ES2022` | Modern target, matches Node 20.x capabilities |
| `moduleResolution` | `bundler` | Next.js 15 recommended setting |

