## 8. Risk Assessment

### 8.1 Technical Risks

| Risk | Probability | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|-------------|--------|------------|
| ESLint 9 flat config compatibility issues | Medium | Low | Use stable plugin versions; fallback to eslintrc if needed |
| TypeScript strict mode breaking third-party types | Low | Medium | Use `skipLibCheck: true` |
| Tailwind CSS variable inheritance issues | Low | Low | Test thoroughly in base layout |
| Husky git hooks not triggering | Low | Medium | Document manual setup for Windows users |

### 8.2 Mitigation Strategies

1. **ESLint Compatibility**: Pin all ESLint plugin versions; test before upgrading
2. **TypeScript**: Start with recommended settings; add stricter rules incrementally
3. **Cross-Platform**: Use LF line endings; document pnpm version requirements

---

## 9. Trade-Offs

### 9.1 Decisions Made

| Decision | Alternative Considered | Why Chosen |
|----------|----------------------|------------|
| `@/` path alias only | Multiple aliases (`@components/`, `@lib/`) | Simplicity; single alias is sufficient |
| ESLint flat config | Legacy `.eslintrc` | Future-proof; ESLint 9 is the standard |
| CSS variables for Tailwind colors | Static color values | Enables ShadCN theming; runtime dark mode |
| Minimal `next.config.ts` | Feature-heavy config | YAGNI; add features when needed |
| `noUncheckedIndexedAccess` enabled | Disabled for convenience | Catches real bugs at the cost of verbosity |

### 9.2 Deferred Decisions

| Topic | Reason | When to Revisit |
|-------|--------|-----------------|
